    <h3 class="center">About Reverse Mortgages</h3>
    <br />
    <p>
        <meta charset="utf-8" />
        <b id="docs-internal-guid-999bbdf0-7fff-f8d7-3752-936c589fd9be" style="font-weight:normal;"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">A reverse mortgage is very different than a typical mortgage. A reverse mortgage is only available to those over 62 years of age. The scenario in which someone would want a reverse mortgage is when a borrower already owns a high value asset but they need more money that can actually be spent. In this case scenario a creditor would take ownership of the borrowers high value asset in exchange for money. Despite the simplicity of this description, reverse mortgages are often ill-advised.&nbsp; </span></b>
    </p>


